 Summary File (QT-PL), Hallam borough, Pennsylvania |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=October 6, 2011 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==History==\nBefore 1736, all parts of Pennsylvania west of the [[Susquehanna River]], including present-day Hallam Borough and the surrounding [[Hellam Township, York County, Pennsylvania|Hellam Township]], were land of the [[Iroquois]].\n\nIn October 1736, the [[Province of Pennsylvania|Proprietors of Pennsylvania]] received from the Five Nations deeds for the Susquehanna lands south of the [[Blue Mountain (Pennsylvania)|Blue Mountain]]s, including the borough and township.\n\nFrom 1736 to 1739, the area was under the authority of Hempfield Township in [[Lancaster County, Pennsylvania|Lancaster County]] east of the Susquehanna. In 1739, the Provincial Assembly passed a special act to empower Lancaster County to establish townships west of the river. Hellam Township was created and included most of what is now [[York County, Pennsylvania|York]], [[Adams County, Pennsylvania|Adams]] and [[Cumberland County, Pennsylvania|Cumberland]] counties. Hellam Township was named after [[Hallamshire]], the township in England where Samuel Blunston, the magistrate of Lancaster County, was born.\n\nWhen Hallam Borough was incorporated in 1902, the town's name was spelled Hallam, the same as the English township.\n\nThe [[Martin Schultz House]] was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1993.<ref name=\"nris\">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\n[[File:U.S. Census Bureau map of Hallam, Pennsylvania.gif|thumb|left|Map of Hallam]]\nHallam is located at {{Coord|40|0|14|N|76|36|16|W|type:city}} (40.003897, -76.604528).<ref name=GAZ>{{Cite web|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/GCTTable?_bm=y&-geo_id=04000US42&-_box_head_nbr=GCT-PH1-R&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U&-_lang=en&-redoLog=false&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_GCTPH1R_ST7S&-format=ST-7S&-_sse=on |title=Pennsylvania Place and County Subdivision |work=[[2000 United States Census]] |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |year=2000 |accessdate=2009-07-16 }}{{dead link|date=September 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> It is a suburb of [[York, Pennsylvania]] and is part of the York-Hanover Metropolitan Statistical Area, as well as the York-Hanover-Gettysburg Combined Statistical Area.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.census.gov/econ/census02/maps/metro/33000us564m.pdf |title=York-Hanover-Gettysburg Combined Statistical Area 2003 |format=[[PDF]] |work=2002 Economic Census |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |year=2002 |access-date=2009-07-16 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121008220911/http://www.census.gov/econ/census02/maps/metro/33000us564m.pdf |archive-date=2012-10-08 |df= }}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the borough has a total area of {{convert|0.7|sqmi|km2}}, all of it land.<ref name=\"GAZ\" />\n\nHallam is located within the [[Kreutz Creek]] watershed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ycpc.org/municipal_current_docs/act167.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050514234850/http://www.ycpc.org/municipal_current_docs/act167.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=2005-05-14|title=Act 167 Stormwater Management Plans Map|date=|format=[[PDF]]|work=Planning Commission|publisher=County of York|access-date=2009-07-16}}</ref>\n\n===Climate===\nHallam lies on the cusp of a [[humid subtropical climate]] zone and experiences four discernible seasons. It receives an average of {{convert|43|in|mm}} of [[Precipitation (meteorology)|precipitation]] each year, with the wettest month being June. In January 1994, Hallam experienced its lowest recorded temperature at -21&nbsp;\u00b0F, while the hottest temperature on record was 105&nbsp;\u00b0F in July 1936.<ref name=TIEMPO>{{Cite web|url=http://www.weather.com/outlook/travel/businesstraveler/wxclimatology/monthly/graph/27929?from=36hr_bottomnav_business|title=Monthly Weather Averages for York, PA|work=Weather.com|publisher=[[The Weather Channel (United States)|The Weather Channel]]|accessdate=2009-07-16}}</ref>\n\n{{Weather box\n|location = Hallam, PA\n|single line = Yes\n|Jan high F = 39\n|Feb high F = 43\n|Mar high F = 53\n|Apr high F = 65\n|May high F = 75\n|Jun high F = 83\n|Jul high F = 87\n|Aug high F = 85\n|Sep high F = 78\n|Oct high F = 67\n|Nov high F = 54\n|Dec high F = 43\n|Jan low F = 21\n|Feb low F = 23\n|Mar low F = 31\n|Apr low F = 39\n|May low F = 49\n|Jun low F = 58\n|Jul low F = 63\n|Aug low F = 61\n|Sep low F = 54\n|Oct low F = 42\n|Nov low F = 34\n|Dec low F = 26\n|Jan precipitation inch = 3.44\n|Feb precipitation inch = 2.77\n|Mar precipitation inch = 3.65\n|Apr precipitation inch = 3.52\n|May precipitation inch = 4.26\n|Jun precipitation inch = 4.31\n|Jul precipitation inch = 3.75\n|Aug precipitation inch = 3.33\n|Sep precipitation inch = 4.1\n|Oct precipitation inch = 3.16\n|Nov precipitation inch = 3.47\n|Dec precipitation inch = 3.24\n|source 1 = [[The Weather Channel (United States)|The Weather Channel]]<ref name=TIEMPO />\n|date = August 2010}}\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1910= 472\n|1920= 492\n|1930= 771\n|1940= 799\n|1950= 976\n|1960= 1234\n|1970= 1825\n|1980= 1428\n|1990= 1375\n|2000= 1532\n|2010= 2673\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=2659\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=December 7, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=Sources:<ref name=\"USDecennialCensus\">{{cite web|title=Census of Population and Housing|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=11 December 2013|df=}}</ref><ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website|df=}}</ref><ref name=CensusPopEst>{{cite web|title=Incorporated Places and Minor Civil Divisions Datasets: Subcounty Resident Population Estimates: April 1, 2010 to July 1, 2012|url=https://www.census.gov/popest/data/cities/totals/2012/SUB-EST2012.html|work=Population Estimates|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=11 December 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130611010502/http://www.census.gov/popest/data/cities/totals/2012/SUB-EST2012.html|archive-date=11 June 2013|df=}}</ref>\n}}\nAs of the [[census]] of 2000, there were 1,532 people, 667 households, and 450 families residing in the borough.<ref name=\"Census\" /> The [[population density]] was 2,182.5 people per square mile (845.0/km\u00b2). There were 713 housing units at an average density of 1,015.7 per square mile (393.3/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the borough was 96.21% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 1.31% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.39% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.59% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.85% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.65% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.31% of the population.<ref name=Census>{{Cite web|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/SAFFFacts?_event=Search&geo_id=16000US1743666&_geoContext=01000US%7C04000US17%7C16000US1743666&_street=&_county=Hallam&_cityTown=Hallam&_state=04000US42&_zip=&_lang=en&_sse=on&ActiveGeoDiv=geoSelect&_useEV=&pctxt=fph&pgsl=160&_submenuId=factsheet_1&ds_name=DEC_2000_SAFF&_ci_nbr=null&qr_name=null&reg=null%3Anull&_keyword=&_industry=|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212051644/http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/SAFFFacts?_event=Search&geo_id=16000US1743666&_geoContext=01000US%7C04000US17%7C16000US1743666&_street=&_county=Hallam&_cityTown=Hallam&_state=04000US42&_zip=&_lang=en&_sse=on&ActiveGeoDiv=geoSelect&_useEV=&pctxt=fph&pgsl=160&_submenuId=factsheet_1&ds_name=DEC_2000_SAFF&_ci_nbr=null&qr_name=null&reg=null:null&_keyword=&_industry=|url-status=dead|archive-date=2020-02-12|title=Hallam, Pennsylvania Fact Sheet|accessdate=2009-07-01|work=[[2000 United States Census]]|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>\n\nThere were 667 households out of which 29.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 54.6% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 9.6% had a female householder with no husband present, and 32.4% were non-families. 25.9% of all households were made up of individuals and 9.4% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.30 and the average family size was 2.76.<ref name=\"Census\" />\n\nIn the borough the population was spread out with 22.3% under the age of 18, 8.0% from 18 to 24, 30.8% from 25 to 44, 24.0% from 45 to 64, and 14.9% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 37 years. For every 100 females there were 97.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 92.4 males.<ref name=\"Census\" />\n\nThe median income for a household in the borough was $42,235, and the median income for a family was $47,552. Males had a median income of $34,773 versus $24,716 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the borough was $22,868. About 5.0% of families and 4.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 5.1% of those under age 18 and 6.7% of those age 65 or over.<ref name=\"Census\" />\n\n==Education==\n[[File:Hallam, Pennsylvania (5655985974).jpg|thumb|upright=1.3|Hallam United Methodist Church]]\nThe Hallam Borough is served by the [[Eastern York School District]]. Students in Hallam go to Kreutz Creek Elementary School if they are in grades K-5, Eastern York Middle School in 6-8, and Eastern York High School in 9-12. Students may also attend one of the Commonwealth's cyber charter schools at no additional cost to the family or student. The local school district pays the state set tuition fee to the cyber charter school that the student chooses to attend. By state law, charter school students have access to all extracurriculars and sports programs at the local public school district. Alternatively, the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania permits parents to home school their children or they may attend a private school.<ref>Pennsylvania Department of Education, Charter Schools, 2013</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*Kreutz Creek Valley Preservation Society, \"An Early History of Hellam Township\"\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [http://www.hallamborough.com/ Hallam Borough official website]\n\n{{York County, Pennsylvania}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1770]]\n[[Category:Boroughs in York County, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:1902 establishments in Pennsylvania]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hallam,_Pennsylvania"}
